Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Cut the @baguette{2} widthways at an angle into 2cm slices.

Lay the bread slices onto a #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste} and season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Toast until golden brown, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Once cooked, top half the slices with @blue cheese{55%g} and a drizzle of
@cranberry chutney{1%sachet}.

Tear @sliced Irish ham{80%g} and drained @mozzarella{125%g} over the remaining
crostini slices.

Season lightly with @salt{tsp} and @pepper{to taste}.

Serve the crostini on #platters{}.

To finish, drizzle the @balsamic glaze{1%sachet} over the top.

> An array of crostini with different delightful toppings to wow guests and
> thrill tastebuds at any occasion.

> Perfect for sharing.